name: github3.py
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "3.2.0" %}

package:
  name: github3.py
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: github3.py-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/g/github3.py/github3.py-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 09b72be1497d346b0968cde8360a0d6af79dc206d0149a63cd3ec86c65c377cc

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - pyjwt >=2.3.0
    - python-dateutil >=2.6.0
    - requests >=2.18
    - typing-extensions >=3.10.0.2
    - uritemplate >=3.0.0

test:
  imports:
    - github3
    - github3.gists
    - github3.issues
    - github3.repos
    - github3.search
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github3py.readthedocs.org
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Python wrapper for the GitHub API (http://developer.github.com/v3).

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jakirkham
    - ocefpaf
    - sigmavirus24
    - scopatz
